    <!-- Exam Strategy -->
    <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-10);">
      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:var(--text-2xl); color:var(--color-brand-dark); margin-bottom:var(--space-5); padding-bottom:var(--space-2); border-bottom:3px solid var(--color-accent);">Exam Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="article-body">
          <h3 style="color:var(--color-brand-dark);">The 3-Phase Approach</h3>
          <p><strong>Phase 1 — Foundation (3-4 months):</strong> Read NCERTs (6-12) + standard books. Build conceptual base for all 4 GS papers.</p>
          <p><strong>Phase 2 — Current Affairs + Integration (ongoing):</strong> Daily newspaper reading + editorial analysis. Link static notes with current events. Use <a href="https://ujiyari.com" target="_blank">Ujiyari.com</a> for daily coverage.</p>
          <p><strong>Phase 3 — Answer Writing + Revision (3-4 months before Mains):</strong> Practice 2-3 answers daily. Revise using BharatNotes topic pages. Solve PYQs under timed conditions.</p>

          <h3 style="color:var(--color-brand-dark);">Key Habits</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Daily:</strong> 1 hour current affairs + 1 editorial analysis</li>
            <li><strong>Weekly:</strong> 2 answer writing practice sessions + 1 Prelims mock</li>
            <li><strong>Monthly:</strong> Full revision of one GS paper + monthly current affairs compilation</li>
            <li><strong>Always:</strong> Maintain a fact sheet for every topic you study (use BharatNotes as your template)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

